# compound-engineering ce-review tooling writes persona findings here; it is
# scratch output, not source. Untracked files in read-only review phases trip
# the orchestrator's mutation guard (see #338 false-positive), so ignore it.
.context/
*.result
*.log
# Per-run orchestrator artifacts written at the repo/worktree root. These must
# never be tracked: the validate phase rewrites *.headsha each run, which would
# otherwise dirty the tree and trip the read-only phase mutation guards.
# Canonical list: scripts/lib/artifacts.sh → orchestrator_artifact_paths()
*.headsha
/review-fix-plan.json
/review-task-manifest.json
/review-triage.md
/code-review.md
/review-loop-history.json
/arbiter-result.json
/compound-draft.md
/fix-validate-done.marker
/plan-review-passed.marker
/review.md
/task-manifest.json
.review-context/
.ai/
changes/
review-reports/
docs/spec-vs-implementation-reviews/
.DS_Store
test-results/
.antigravitycli/
.claude/
cache/
.ai-orchestrator.local.json
/result.json
task-*-complete.md

# Stray agent/orchestrator scratch that has leaked into commits before
# (full_diff.patch #161, review-plan-task-5.md #334). See #280/#314/#405.
# Canonical exclude list lives in scripts/lib/artifacts.sh → orchestrator_artifact_paths();
# these patterns are belt-and-suspenders against per-task scratch leaking from worktree roots.
/full_diff.patch
/diff.patch
/review-plan-task-*.md
/quality-review-task-*.md
/quality-review-task-*.result
/spec-review-task-*.md
/spec-review-task-*.result
/fix-review-task-*.md
/fix-review-task-*.result
/implementation-log.md
